- Too Low for Zero is a fine record with strong singles and energetic production, but its early‑80s AOR/pop production emphasizes punchy, era‑specific sonics and stand‑out tracks rather than the same kind of cohesive, intimate album flow Tapestry provides. Given only the general preference for enjoying CDs (without any stated genre bias), Tapestry is the safer, more broadly rewarding choice for extended, album‑focused listening—so I select Tapestry and decline Too Low for Zero for this purpose.

