The user updates his self-description as follows: I prefer intimate, piano‑anchored studio records: a mic‑forward grand piano with tactile key attack, dead‑center close‑forward uncrushed lead vocals, and analogue‑warm, low‑compression mastering that preserves transient snap, micro‑dynamics and generous headroom. Sparse percussion, minimal overdubs, restrained low‑reverb close harmonies, melody‑first sequencing and concise 3–4‑minute songs are central — mixes that reward close, focused listening.
From earlier tastes I retain a liking for clear instrument separation, subtle hiss reduction that keeps air, tactile but supportive bass/drums, and vocal immediacy that feels “people in the room.” I also value low‑stacked arrangements where a single conversational vocal carries the song.
